# Air movement

#### Heavily influenced by [[Unsorted/The Sun\|The Sun]]
- Land and water absorb solar energy

## Convection
- Warm air/water rises, creating vertical currents
- Air expands/cools at higher pressure
	- Cooler air proceeds to sink
	- Moisture condenses, resulting in [[Unsorted/The Water Cycle#Precipitation\|Precipitation]]

#### Thermal Inversion Layers
- Can trap pollutants below the troposphere
- Results from alternating hot-cool layers
	- Prevents vertical mixing
	- ![Pasted image 20221115185040.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)

# Ozone
![Pasted image 20221115191830.png|100](data:image/png;base64,)![Pasted image 20221115191848.png|200](data:image/png;base64,)

- Occurs in 2 layers:
	- Troposphere (0-10mi)
		- Ground level, "bad" ozone
		- Pollutant, harms plants and animals
		- Major component of urban smog
	- Stratosphere (10-30mi)
		- Protects life on earth by filtering out UV-B rays from [[Unsorted/The Sun\|The Sun]]
- In general, bad when breathed, good in upper atmosphere
